Package: rfuji
Title: Assess the FAIRness of Research Data Objects
Version: 2.3.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ahmad", "Sofi-Mahmudi", email = "a.sofimahmudi@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-6829-0823")),
    person("Steffen", "Neumann", email = "sneumann@ipb-halle.de", role = "aut",
           comment = "Author of the original rfuji F-UJI API client"),
    person("PANGAEA", role = "cph",
           comment = "Copyright holder of the F-UJI service whose metrics rfuji reimplements"))
Description: A native R implementation of the F-UJI (FAIRsFAIR Research Data
    Object Assessment) metrics for evaluating how well a research data object
    satisfies the FAIR principles (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable,
    Reusable). Given a persistent identifier or URL, rfuji resolves it,
    harvests metadata from landing pages and registries, and scores it against
    the FAIRsFAIR metrics (<doi:10.5281/zenodo.3775793>) entirely in R, without
    requiring an external assessment server.
